			<title>Microsoft Wants to Build the Lawnmower Man</title>
			<link>http://www.papelmag.com/tecnocrata/153-microsoft-wants-to-build-the-lawnmower-man.html</link>
			<guid>http://www.papelmag.com/tecnocrata/153-microsoft-wants-to-build-the-lawnmower-man.html</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><img hspace="5" width="100%" vspace="5" border="0" align="left" alt="Bill Gates is The Lawnmower Man" src="http://www.papelmag.com/images/stories/tecnocrata/microsoft_wants_to_build_the_lawnmower_man/lawnmowerman.jpg" /></p>
<p style="text-align: right;">&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;<span>Men are only as good as their technical development allows them to be.&quot;<br />
</span></strong><span>--- George Orwell</span></p>
<p align="right"><b>&ldquo;Just because you&rsquo;re paranoid doesn&rsquo;t mean they aren&rsquo;t after you&rdquo;<br />
</b>--- Kurt Cobain</p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bill Gates may be planning on living forever as the Lawnmower Man. I am not shitting you. All evidence points towards that end if we browse through the patents Microsoft&rsquo;s Research and Development team has been working on for the past three years. The pieces are slowly starting to fit, and it&rsquo;s either that or he&rsquo;s making Skynet&rsquo;s road to Armageddon a wee bit easier.</p>
]]></description>
