			<title>Pandora: The Bane of the DJ</title>
			<link>http://www.papelmag.com/tecnocrata/85-pandora-the-bane-of-the-dj.html</link>
			<guid>http://www.papelmag.com/tecnocrata/85-pandora-the-bane-of-the-dj.html</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><img width="150" height="150" vspace="5" hspace="5" border="0" align="left" alt="" src="http://www.papelmag.com/images/stories/tecnocrata/pandora/logo_pandora.png" />According to mythology, Pandora was the first woman created by the gods as the silky seductress that would lead men to their own destruction. Such punishment came after Prometheus had given man the fire of wisdom, through which they were attempting at playing gods themselves. By opening, out of curiosity, a jar; she let loose all the evils that were contained inside it upon the world letting Hope be the only thing left in the jar, later infamously known as Pandora&rsquo;s Box.</p>
]]></description>
